text.tspan: • Work with more complex point clouds
• Reduce memory usage of the CSG tree
In this work we provide a method to extract and render geometric primitives from point clouds, without
the need to convert to polygon meshes. The extraction is realized in two steps: first the basic shapes are
detected, then their boundaries are analyzed and stored in a convenient spatial data-structure. Finally, a
ray-tracer is employed to directly visualize the extracted primitives.
